Sluitingsdatum: 2 april 2023
Beschrijving:
Will you help us shape the future?

Amsterdam University of Applied Sciences (AUAS) is looking for an enthusiastic colleague who would like to join us in the role of

Educational Officer (0.8 FTE)

Quantum technology is a breakthrough field based on the behaviour of the smallest particles. Expectations are high due to the new methods of computation, communication and measurement made possible by this technology. The first commercial applications are already available, but the real breakthrough is only expected a few years from now with respect to potential applications for the climate, new materials, medicines, optimisation, cybersecurity, communication and sensing. The Netherlands is in a unique position to play an important role in the development of this technology and thus gain an economic advantage.
With funding available from the growth fund, Quantum Delta Nederland (QDNL) has set up a broad programme which includes research, ecosystem development, education and ethical, legal and social issues. As part of this programme, a Talent and Learning Centre (TLC) has been established in Amsterdam. This TLC is tasked with developing transparent education focused on quantum technology for students, businesses, research institutes and government authorities to be taught at universities, universities of applied sciences, senior secondary vocational education institutions, secondary schools and primary schools, in consultation with national and international partners.

Where will you be working?
You will work in a team of passionate people with different backgrounds in terms of education and experience, who are all enthusiastic about quantum technology. Your workplace will be on the Amstel Campus and sometimes also at Amsterdam Science Park. The team has an open and warm work ethos with plenty of room to share ideas and learn from each other. The TLC has a place within the dynamic ecosystem that Quantum.Amsterdam is creating.

Talent as the basis, diversity as a strength
The AUAS organisation wants everyone in it to feel welcome, appreciated and at home. As an employer, we believe that the more inclusive we are, the better we will be able to perform as a knowledge institution in and for the city. We strive to ensure that the composition of our workforce is a good reflection of the diversity of backgrounds and perspectives that characterise Amsterdam. Regardless of your gender, age, cultural background, who you love and what you believe: you are warmly invited to apply!

What will you be doing?
As an educational officer, you will be responsible for designing education in the field of quantum technology or helping others to do so;
You will contact and consult with external partners involved in education in the Amsterdam region as well as nationally and internationally;
You will maintain a network of relationships between the TLC, the testbeds and the field labs in order to connect the research and projects carried out there with education within the programmes involved;
You will initiate, improve and maintain quantum technology education for programmes in primary schools to university level and beyond;
You will consult with educational officers at the TLCs in Leiden/Delft, Twente and Eindhoven;
You will develop an overview of education in the field of quantum technology in the Amsterdam region and identify how these programmes relate to each other;
You will collaborate on the creation of a website highlighting quantum technology education in the Amsterdam region.

About you
You have a Master’s degree in physics or computer science;
You have knowledge of and experience within the different types of education you’ll be working with;
You have an inquisitive attitude, which means you are curious, critical, eager to understand and willing to change your perspective;
You are well aware of the various challenges in this field and can’t wait to start tackling them. You encourage discussion about this between the parties involved.
You have at least a B2 level in English.

What we have to offer you
First of all, a great place to work in a friendly and driven team;
A temporary appointment for one year. If we are happy with your performance and you are enjoying your work, we will discuss the possibility of extending your appointment with you;
The activities come under the organisational job classification of lecturer/researcher 2. This job is remunerated at salary scale 11 (Collective Labour Agreement for Universities of Applied Sciences). The maximum gross monthly salary for this position is €5,332 for a full-time appointment and is dependent on education and experience.
An extensive package of fringe benefits, including generous leave entitlement, a 13th month and high-quality sports facilities;
Excellent opportunities for training and development. We value your continued professionalisation and therefore offer resources such as our AUAS Academy and our online learning environment GoodHabitz, where you’ll have free unlimited access to all available training courses.

Would you like to find out more about this challenging position?
Please feel free to contact: Marten Teitsma (m.teitsma@hva.nl +31621156982). This email address should only be used to ask questions: we will only process applications received via the application link below.

Would you like to apply?
Your letter of application is your opportunity to persuade us that you are the ideal candidate! To apply for this position, please click on the link below before the 3th of April.

What else you need to know
This vacancy has been published both internally and externally at the same time. Where two candidates are equally suitable for the post, internal candidates will take priority over external candidates.
If you would like to know more about how our application procedure works, see our website WerkenbijdeHvA.nl.
Interviews will be held starting in the week of 17th of April 2023.
No recruitment agencies please.

About the project
We seek a highly motivated PhD candidate for a position in a project concerning the identification of biomarkers for successful treatment discontinuation for patients with Chronic Myeloid leukemia.

About the role
As a PhD student on this project your main tasks will be:
Planning, optimization and performance of experiments using patient-derived samples;
Data analysis and interpretation;
Supervision of Bachelor and Master students during their interships;
Collaboration with partnering labs;
Working closely with, and supervising of, research technicians working on this project;
Writing a PhD thesis based on high-quality internationally peer reviewed publications;
Training in computational biology;
Presentation of findings at (inter)national conferences.
Profile
We seek a highly motivated, enthousiastic and ambitious PhD candidate with a MSc title in Biomedical Science or Medicine, or a PhD student that will be awarded a MSc title at short notice;
You have a background in cell biology/Immunology and an interest in translational cancer research;
You have the capacity and team spirit to closely collaborate with all researchers and medical specialists witin our department as well as with biostatiscians within Amsterdam UMC;
In addition to good cooperation skills, you have good communication skills.
Our offer
Salary Scale OIO: 2.789 to 3.536 euro gross when employed full-time (step depending on qualifications and experience).
A contract for one year (12 months) with the intention to extend for another 36 months.
Besides a good basic salary, you will also receive an 8.3% year-end bonus and 8% holiday allowance.
Free and unlimited access to our online learning environment GoodHabitz.
Pension accrual with ABP, of which pay 70% of the premium.
Reimbursemen tof 75% of your public transport costs. Would you rather travel by bike? Then we have a good bicycle scheme.
An active personnel association and the Young Amsterdam UMC association, which organise fun (sports) activities and events.
About the workplace
Your working environment: The department of Hematology at Amsterdam UMC, chaired by Prof. Sonja Zweegman, location VUmc is specialized in the treatment of patients with hematological malignancies. Within the Hematology laboratory, of the Cancer Center Amsterdam, researchers are investigating leukemia at the molecular level, in close collaboration with the clinicians. The culture is open and cooperation generally low key. Moreover, we strive for equal opportunities for everyone. This means that there is room for everyone’s culture, origin, ideas and creativity.

Let's meet
For information about the contents of the project, please contact Prof dr. J. Cloos, Translational Hematology, via 020-44443838.
For more information about the application procedure, please contact Chey Edwards, Recruitment Advisor, via c.i.edwards@amsterdamumc.nl or via 06-21487245.
A reference check, screening and hiring test may be part of the procedure. Read here whether that applies to you. If you join us, we ask you for a VOG (Certificate of Good Conduct).
Internal candidates will be given priority over external candidates in case of equal suitability.
Acquisition in response to this vacancy is not appreciated.
